claim.claim-text:
[Amended]
A method of extracting a single disc from the bottom of a stack of pre-lubricated discs, the method comprising:
reciprocating an extractor shaft to contact the stack of discs;
retaining and sliding a spindle within the extractor shaft;
mounting a vacuum pad at the upper end of the spindle;
switching on a vacuum supply through the vacuum spindle and into the vacuum pad on the up stroke, and thereby gripping the bottom disc of the stack;
pulling down the gripped disc on the down stroke and breaking any attraction between the bottom disc and the adjacent disc by deformation of the disc shape;
switching off the vacuum supply and releasing the disc.
